<div id='contact-12690'>bencreekin (12690)</div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
Paddled Shavers Fork 8/5/2010, McGee Run to Bowden. The level was 450cfs at Cheat Bridge and<br/>
1300cfs at Bowden. This was a great level, no scraping and not pushy. I think we counted less than<br/>
5 (small)pools we had to paddle across. 20+miles of great waves and play with a few challenging<br/>
rapids to keep your attention. No wood issues currently. Fantastic run. </div>
</td>
</tr>
